Collections - ArrayList : mean

Write a method named mean that accepts as a parameter an ArrayList of real numbers, and returns the arithmetic mean (average) of the integers in the list as a real number. 
For example, if the list passed contains {2.0, 4.5, 6.5, 1.0}, your method should return 3.5.
If the list is empty, return 0.0. Do not modify the list that is passed in.



 public static double mean(ArrayList<Double> numbers) {
        double sum = 0.0;
        double size = numbers.size();
        if(numbers.isEmpty()) {
            return sum;
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < numbers.size(); i++) {
            sum += numbers.get(i);
        }
        return sum / size;
    }
